Using your local validator:

1. Install the validator: http://validator.w3.org/docs/install.html
2. (Optional) Install the HTML 5 validator: http://about.validator.nu/
3. Install the (tweaked) "WebService-Validator-HTML-W3C" Perl module: https://github.com/chimo/webservice-validator-html-w3c
4. Change the url to your own validator on the line that says: $v->validator_uri("http://localhost/w3c-validator/check");
5. Visit "batchValid.html" in your browser, put your URIs in the textbox separated by newlines and click the button

Using validator.w3.org:

1. Install the (tweaked) "WebService-Validator-HTML-W3C" Perl module: https://github.com/chimo/webservice-validator-html-w3c
2. Comment out the line that says:  $v->validator_uri("http://localhost/w3c-validator/check");
3. Visit "batchValid.html" in your browser, put your URIs in the textbox separated by newlines and click the button
